Note: ============================================================================
Note: KYBER NTT (FIPS 203 Algorithm 9 / 10)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "kyber_ntt_forward" takes poly as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Forward NTT for a Kyber polynomial. Operates in-place on a 256-element
    int16 array stored as 256 * 2 = 512 bytes. Per FIPS 203 Algorithm 9.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Standard Cooley-Tukey forward NTT with 7 layers (len = 128, 64, 32, 16,
    8, 4, 2). Twiddles are fetched from kyber_zeta in bit-reversed order.
    Each butterfly uses Montgomery multiplication so all results live in
    Montgomery domain after the transform.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    7 * 128 = 896 butterflies per polynomial. Each butterfly is 1 mont-mul,
    1 add, 1 sub.
    @End Implementation
    @Security_Scope
    Coefficients may be secret; algorithm is constant-time (no data branches).
    @End Security_Scope
    Let q be 3329
    Let k_idx be 1
    Let length be 128
    While length is greater than or equal to 2:
        Let start_idx be 0
        While start_idx is less than 256:
            Let zeta be proc kyber_zeta with k_idx
            Set k_idx to k_idx plus 1
            Let j be start_idx
            Let end_j be start_idx plus length
            While j is less than end_j:
                Let off_j be j multiplied by 2
                Let off_jl be (j plus length) multiplied by 2
                Let v_jl be Memory.memory_get_int16(poly, off_jl)
                Let prod be v_jl multiplied by zeta
                Let t be proc montgomery_reduce_kyber with prod
                Let v_j be Memory.memory_get_int16(poly, off_j)
                Let new_jl be v_j minus t
                If new_jl is less than 0:
                    Set new_jl to new_jl plus q
                End If
                If new_jl is greater than or equal to q:
                    Set new_jl to new_jl minus q
                End If
                Let new_j be v_j plus t
                If new_j is greater than or equal to q:
                    Set new_j to new_j minus q
                End If
                Memory.memory_set_int16(poly, off_jl, new_jl)
                Memory.memory_set_int16(poly, off_j, new_j)
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
            Set start_idx to start_idx plus length plus length
        End While
        Set length to length divided by 2
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "kyber_ntt_inverse" takes poly as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Inverse NTT for a Kyber polynomial. In-place on 512-byte int16 buffer.
    Per FIPS 203 Algorithm 10.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Gentleman-Sande inverse butterfly across 7 layers (len = 2, 4, 8, 16,
    32, 64, 128). Final scaling by n^{-1} * R mod q (= 1441 for Kyber).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Symmetric to kyber_ntt_forward.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let q be 3329
    Let f_scaler be 1441
    Let k_idx be 127
    Let length be 2
    While length is less than or equal to 128:
        Let start_idx be 0
        While start_idx is less than 256:
            Let zeta be proc kyber_zeta with k_idx
            Set k_idx to k_idx minus 1
            Let j be start_idx
            Let end_j be start_idx plus length
            While j is less than end_j:
                Let off_j be j multiplied by 2
                Let off_jl be (j plus length) multiplied by 2
                Let v_j be Memory.memory_get_int16(poly, off_j)
                Let v_jl be Memory.memory_get_int16(poly, off_jl)
                Let t be v_j
                Let sum_v be t plus v_jl
                If sum_v is greater than or equal to q:
                    Set sum_v to sum_v minus q
                End If
                Memory.memory_set_int16(poly, off_j, sum_v)
                Let diff_v be v_jl minus t
                Let mont_input be diff_v multiplied by zeta
                Let new_jl be proc montgomery_reduce_kyber with mont_input
                If new_jl is less than 0:
                    Set new_jl to new_jl plus q
                End If
                Memory.memory_set_int16(poly, off_jl, new_jl)
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
            Set start_idx to start_idx plus length plus length
        End While
        Set length to length multiplied by 2
    End While
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 256:
        Let off_i be i multiplied by 2
        Let v_i be Memory.memory_get_int16(poly, off_i)
        Let scaled be v_i multiplied by f_scaler
        Let red be proc montgomery_reduce_kyber with scaled
        If red is less than 0:
            Set red to red plus q
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_int16(poly, off_i, red)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "kyber_base_case_multiply" takes a0 as Integer, a1 as Integer, b0 as Integer, b1 as Integer, zeta as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Multiplies two degree-1 polynomials (a0 + a1*X) * (b0 + b1*X) modulo
    (X^2 - zeta) in Z_q[X]. Used by ml_kem during polynomial product in NTT
    domain. Returns the low half in the global int via the caller-supplied
    out_ptr -- here we expose only the c0 part (and the caller calls again
    for c1 with permuted args) to stay within the 5-arg stage1 limit.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    c0 = a0*b0 + a1*b1*zeta. All multiplications go through Montgomery
    reduction so inputs/outputs live in Montgomery domain.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two Mont-muls + one add per coefficient.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let q be 3329
    Let term1 be a0 multiplied by b0
    Let m1 be proc montgomery_reduce_kyber with term1
    Let prod_a1b1 be a1 multiplied by b1
    Let m_a1b1 be proc montgomery_reduce_kyber with prod_a1b1
    Let term2 be m_a1b1 multiplied by zeta
    Let m2 be proc montgomery_reduce_kyber with term2
    Let c0 be m1 plus m2
    If c0 is greater than or equal to q:
        Set c0 to c0 minus q
    End If
    If c0 is less than 0:
        Set c0 to c0 plus q
    End If
    Return c0
End Process

Process called "kyber_base_case_multiply_c1" takes a0 as Integer, a1 as Integer, b0 as Integer, b1 as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Companion to kyber_base_case_multiply returning c1 = a0*b1 + a1*b0.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Two Montgomery multiplications then add modulo q.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Two Mont-muls + one add.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let q be 3329
    Let t1 be a0 multiplied by b1
    Let m1 be proc montgomery_reduce_kyber with t1
    Let t2 be a1 multiplied by b0
    Let m2 be proc montgomery_reduce_kyber with t2
    Let c1 be m1 plus m2
    If c1 is greater than or equal to q:
        Set c1 to c1 minus q
    End If
    If c1 is less than 0:
        Set c1 to c1 plus q
    End If
    Return c1
End Process

Process called "kyber_pointwise_multiply" takes a_poly as Integer, b_poly as Integer, out_poly as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    NTT-domain multiplication of two polynomials. For Kyber the NTT is split
    into 128 base cases of degree-1, each multiplied modulo X^2 - zeta where
    the zeta is the "second-stage" twiddle. Implements FIPS 203 Algorithm 11.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    For i in 0..127: zeta_i = kyber_zeta(64 + i). Apply base case multiply
    to coefficient pairs (2i, 2i+1). Use sign flipping for odd-index
    coset twiddles per the reference table convention.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    256 Montgomery muls total.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 128:
        Let zeta_i be proc kyber_zeta with 64 plus i
        If (i bitwise_and 1) is equal to 1:
            Set zeta_i to 0 minus zeta_i
        End If
        Let off_lo be i multiplied by 4
        Let off_hi be off_lo plus 2
        Let a0 be Memory.memory_get_int16(a_poly, off_lo)
        Let a1 be Memory.memory_get_int16(a_poly, off_hi)
        Let b0 be Memory.memory_get_int16(b_poly, off_lo)
        Let b1 be Memory.memory_get_int16(b_poly, off_hi)
        Let c0 be proc kyber_base_case_multiply with a0, a1, b0, b1, zeta_i
        Let c1 be proc kyber_base_case_multiply_c1 with a0, a1, b0, b1
        Memory.memory_set_int16(out_poly, off_lo, c0)
        Memory.memory_set_int16(out_poly, off_hi, c1)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note:
DILITHIUM ZETA TABLE

Powers of zeta = 1753 (primitive 512-th root of unity mod 8380417) in
bit-reversed Montgomery form (R = 2^32). Values from pq-crystals
reference implementation. 256 entries.
:End Note

Process called "dilithium_zeta" takes index as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Returns the index-th Dilithium twiddle in Montgomery domain (R = 2^32).
    Indexed 0..255. Table from pq-crystals dilithium reference.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Ladder of If checks over a small fixed table. We delegate the actual
    constant fetches to dilithium_zeta_block_a, _b, _c, _d helpers to keep
    each ladder under the codegen branch limit.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Constant-time lookup; predictable branch pattern under sequential access.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Index derived from public loop counters.
    @End Security_Scope
    If index is less than 64:
        Return proc dilithium_zeta_block_a with index
    End If
    If index is less than 128:
        Return proc dilithium_zeta_block_b with index minus 64
    End If
    If index is less than 192:
        Return proc dilithium_zeta_block_c with index minus 128
    End If
    Return proc dilithium_zeta_block_d with index minus 192
End Process

