Note: ============================================================================
Note: DILITHIUM NTT (FIPS 204 Algorithm 41 / 42)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "dilithium_ntt_forward" takes poly as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Forward NTT for a Dilithium polynomial. In-place on a 256-element int32
    array stored as 1024 bytes (256 * 4). Per FIPS 204 Algorithm 41.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Cooley-Tukey across 8 layers (len = 128..1). Each butterfly applies
    Montgomery reduction modulo q = 8380417.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    8 * 128 = 1024 butterflies; each is one 64x32 multiplication followed by
    a Montgomery reduction.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let q be 8380417
    Let k_idx be 0
    Let length be 128
    While length is greater than or equal to 1:
        Let start_idx be 0
        While start_idx is less than 256:
            Set k_idx to k_idx plus 1
            Let zeta be proc dilithium_zeta with k_idx
            Let j be start_idx
            Let end_j be start_idx plus length
            While j is less than end_j:
                Let off_j be j multiplied by 4
                Let off_jl be (j plus length) multiplied by 4
                Let v_jl be Memory.memory_get_int32(poly, off_jl)
                Let prod be v_jl multiplied by zeta
                Let t be proc montgomery_reduce_dilithium with prod
                Let v_j be Memory.memory_get_int32(poly, off_j)
                Let new_jl be v_j minus t
                Let new_j be v_j plus t
                Memory.memory_set_int32(poly, off_jl, new_jl)
                Memory.memory_set_int32(poly, off_j, new_j)
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
            Set start_idx to start_idx plus length plus length
        End While
        Set length to length divided by 2
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "dilithium_ntt_inverse" takes poly as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Inverse NTT for a Dilithium polynomial. Per FIPS 204 Algorithm 42.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Gentleman-Sande inverse with len = 1..128, then final multiplication by
    f = 41978 (= mont(1/256) mod q).
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Symmetric to dilithium_ntt_forward.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let q be 8380417
    Let f_scaler be 41978
    Let k_idx be 256
    Let length be 1
    While length is less than 256:
        Let start_idx be 0
        While start_idx is less than 256:
            Set k_idx to k_idx minus 1
            Let zeta be 0 minus proc dilithium_zeta with k_idx
            Let j be start_idx
            Let end_j be start_idx plus length
            While j is less than end_j:
                Let off_j be j multiplied by 4
                Let off_jl be (j plus length) multiplied by 4
                Let v_j be Memory.memory_get_int32(poly, off_j)
                Let v_jl be Memory.memory_get_int32(poly, off_jl)
                Let t be v_j
                Let sum_v be t plus v_jl
                Memory.memory_set_int32(poly, off_j, sum_v)
                Let diff_v be t minus v_jl
                Let mont_input be diff_v multiplied by zeta
                Let new_jl be proc montgomery_reduce_dilithium with mont_input
                Memory.memory_set_int32(poly, off_jl, new_jl)
                Set j to j plus 1
            End While
            Set start_idx to start_idx plus length plus length
        End While
        Set length to length multiplied by 2
    End While
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 256:
        Let off_i be i multiplied by 4
        Let v_i be Memory.memory_get_int32(poly, off_i)
        Let scaled be v_i multiplied by f_scaler
        Let red be proc montgomery_reduce_dilithium with scaled
        If red is less than 0:
            Set red to red plus q
        End If
        Memory.memory_set_int32(poly, off_i, red)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Process called "dilithium_pointwise_multiply" takes a_poly as Integer, b_poly as Integer, out_poly as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    NTT-domain pointwise multiplication of two Dilithium polynomials. Since
    X^256+1 splits completely modulo q, this is plain pointwise multiplication
    followed by Montgomery reduction.
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Per FIPS 204 Algorithm 45: 256 independent montgomery multiplies.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    256 reductions.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    Constant-time.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let i be 0
    While i is less than 256:
        Let off_i be i multiplied by 4
        Let a_v be Memory.memory_get_int32(a_poly, off_i)
        Let b_v be Memory.memory_get_int32(b_poly, off_i)
        Let prod be a_v multiplied by b_v
        Let c_v be proc montgomery_reduce_dilithium with prod
        Memory.memory_set_int32(out_poly, off_i, c_v)
        Set i to i plus 1
    End While
    Return 1
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: COMPRESS / DECOMPRESS (FIPS 203 4.5 -- used by ML-KEM ByteEncode)
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "kyber_compress" takes x as Integer, d as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Compress_d(x) = round((2^d / q) * x) mod 2^d. Per FIPS 203 Eq (4.7).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    Uses the constant-time identity ((x << d) + (q+1)/2) / q. Result wrapped
    to d bits.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single 64-bit multiplication/division per coefficient.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    No data-dependent branches.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let q be 3329
    Let half_q be 1665
    Let shifted be x shifted left by d
    Let summed be shifted plus half_q
    Let quotient be summed divided by q
    Let mask be 1 shifted left by d
    Set mask to mask minus 1
    Return quotient bitwise_and mask
End Process

Process called "kyber_decompress" takes y as Integer, d as Integer returns Integer:
    @Reasoning
    Decompress_d(y) = round((q / 2^d) * y). Per FIPS 203 Eq (4.8).
    @End Reasoning
    @Implementation
    (y * q + (1 << (d-1))) >> d.
    @End Implementation
    @Performance_Hints
    Single mul + shift.
    @End Performance_Hints
    @Security_Scope
    No data branches.
    @End Security_Scope
    Let q be 3329
    Let half be 1 shifted left by d minus 1
    Let scaled be y multiplied by q
    Set scaled to scaled plus half
    Return scaled shifted right by d
End Process
